---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Features | Boat & RV Guardian">
	<section class="page-hero">
		<div class="container">
			<span class="eyebrow">Features</span>
			<h1>Everything Guardian watches</h1>
			<p>A closer look at how an open-source app and a handful of off-the-shelf sensors keep your vessel or rig safe from floods, dead batteries, and power loss.</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<div class="container main-content">

		<!-- 1. Water Shutoff -->
		<section class="feature-block">
			<div class="content">
				<div class="icon-badge">💧</div>
				<h2>Automatic water shutoff</h2>
				<p>Never come home to a flooded cabin. Guardian integrates deeply with LinkTap smart valves to stop a burst line before it does real damage.</p>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>Real-time flow metering:</strong> See exactly how many gallons are moving through your plumbing, second by second.</li>
					<li><strong>Volume &amp; rate limits:</strong> Set a ceiling on usage — if a fitting fails and flow runs away, the valve closes itself.</li>
					<li><strong>Remote control:</strong> Open or close your main water line from anywhere in the world.</li>
					<li><strong>Local control:</strong> The LinkTap Gateway is driven directly on your network, with no cloud latency when you're aboard.</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
			<div class="visual glass-card">
				<div class="mockup-image" style="background-image: url('/mobile-alert.png');"></div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- 2. Power Monitoring -->
		<section class="feature-block row-reverse">
			<div class="content">
				<div class="icon-badge">⚡</div>
				<h2>12V battery &amp; shore power health</h2>
				<p>Your rig runs on its 12V system. Guardian keeps a constant eye on it so you never wake up to a dead bank or a thawed fridge.</p>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>Precision voltage tracking:</strong> Graph house and starter banks over time and catch deep discharge early.</li>
					<li><strong>Shore power status:</strong> Know the instant a marina or campground pedestal drops AC.</li>
					<li><strong>Climate awareness:</strong> Temperature and humidity monitoring is on the roadmap to fight mold and frozen pipes.</li>
					<li><strong>Reliable hardware:</strong> Built on the low-power Shelly Plus Uni and Shelly PM Mini Gen3.</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
			<div class="visual glass-card">
				<div class="stat-card">
					<div class="stat-row"><span>🔋 House Bank</span><span class="status-ok">13.2 V · Charging</span></div>
					<div class="stat-row"><span>🔌 Starter Bank</span><span class="status-ok">12.8 V · Healthy</span></div>
					<div class="stat-row"><span>⚡ Shore Power</span><span class="status-ok">Connected · 118 V</span></div>
					<div class="stat-row"><span>🌡️ Cabin</span><span class="status-muted">68°F · 44% RH</span></div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- 3. Cloud Alerts -->
		<section class="feature-block">
			<div class="content">
				<div class="icon-badge">🚨</div>
				<h2>Bilge &amp; high-water alarms</h2>
				<p>Shelly Flood Gen4 sensors plus a Cloudflare Worker mean the alert reaches you the second water shows up — no fragile hub in the middle.</p>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>Direct webhook receivers:</strong> Sensors fire straight to our edge network, bypassing flaky cloud hubs.</li>
					<li><strong>Instant push notifications:</strong> Get alerted on iOS or Android the moment a leak or power failure is detected.</li>
					<li><strong>Automated emergency actions:</strong> A critical alert can trigger the LinkTap valve to close remotely, limiting damage while you're away.</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
			<div class="visual glass-card">
				<div class="mockup-image" style="background-image: url('/flood_warning.png');"></div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- 4. Local First Architecture -->
		<section class="feature-block row-reverse">
			<div class="content">
				<div class="icon-badge">🏠</div>
				<h2>Local-first &amp; private</h2>
				<p>Off-grid, your safety systems shouldn't fall apart just because there's no cell signal. Guardian is built to run on your own network first.</p>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>Zero-latency local API:</strong> On the same Wi-Fi as your sensors, the dashboard talks to them directly — no internet needed.</li>
					<li><strong>Privacy by default:</strong> Real-time data stays on your local network unless you choose to enable cloud sync.</li>
					<li><strong>Seamless cloud fallback:</strong> Leave the dock and the app switches to cloud polling so you keep control from afar.</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
			<div class="visual glass-card">
				<div class="stat-card">
					<div class="stat-row"><span>📶 Mode</span><span class="status-ok">Local · On network</span></div>
					<div class="stat-row"><span>⏱️ Poll latency</span><span class="status-ok">1.2 s</span></div>
					<div class="stat-row"><span>☁️ Cloud sync</span><span class="status-muted">Off (private)</span></div>
					<div class="stat-row"><span>🔒 Data location</span><span class="status-muted">Your network only</span></div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- 5. Open Source Apps -->
		<section class="feature-block">
			<div class="content">
				<div class="icon-badge">💻</div>
				<h2>Free core, open-source, everywhere</h2>
				<p>The core app is free and open-source — you only pay for the hardware you choose. Advanced features may become optional paid add-ons down the road to help sustain the project.</p>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>Desktop native (Tauri):</strong> A lightweight, fast app for macOS and Windows — perfect for the nav station.</li>
					<li><strong>Mobile native (Capacitor):</strong> Android APK with real native push notifications.</li>
					<li><strong>Web dashboard:</strong> Launch instantly in any browser, nothing to install.</li>
					<li><strong>GPL-3.0 licensed:</strong> Inspect it, build it, fork it, or contribute back on GitHub.</li>
				</ul>
				<a href="/devices" class="btn btn-outline" style="margin-top: 0.5rem;">See supported hardware &amp; costs &rarr;</a>
			</div>
			<div class="visual glass-card">
				<div class="mockup-image" style="background-image: url('/hero-dashboard.png'); background-position: left;"></div>
				<span class="visual-caption">Illustrative preview — the actual app may look different.</span>
			</div>
		</section>

	</div>
</Layout>

<style>
	.feature-block {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1.1fr 1fr;
		gap: 4rem;
		align-items: center;
		margin-bottom: 6rem;
	}

	.feature-block.row-reverse { direction: rtl; }
	.feature-block.row-reverse > * { direction: ltr; }

	.icon-badge {
		font-size: 2rem;
		margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
		background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
		width: 64px;
		height: 64px;
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		border-radius: 16px;
		border: 1px solid var(--surface-border);
	}

	.feature-block h2 {
		font-size: 2rem;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
		color: #fff;
	}

	.feature-block .content > p {
		font-size: 1.1rem;
		color: var(--text-muted);
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
		line-height: 1.7;
	}

	.feature-block ul {
		list-style: none;
		padding: 0;
		margin: 0 0 1rem;
	}

	.feature-block ul li {
		position: relative;
		padding-left: 2rem;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
		font-size: 1rem;
		color: #e2e8f0;
		line-height: 1.55;
	}

	.feature-block ul li::before {
		content: "✓";
		position: absolute;
		left: 0;
		color: var(--accent-color);
		font-size: 1.1rem;
		font-weight: bold;
	}

	.feature-block ul li strong { color: #fff; }

	.visual {
		min-height: 340px;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		justify-content: center;
		padding: 1.5rem;
	}

	.mockup-image {
		width: 100%;
		min-height: 380px;
		background-size: cover;
		background-position: center;
		border-radius: 10px;
		border: 1px solid var(--surface-border);
	}

	.visual-caption {
		display: block;
		text-align: center;
		margin-top: 1rem;
		font-size: 0.8rem;
		font-style: italic;
		color: var(--text-muted);
	}

	.stat-card {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 0.75rem;
		width: 100%;
	}

	.stat-row {
		display: flex;
		justify-content: space-between;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 1rem;
		padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
		background: rgba(11, 15, 25, 0.5);
		border: 1px solid var(--surface-border);
		border-radius: 10px;
		font-size: 0.95rem;
	}

	.stat-row > span:first-child { color: var(--text-main); font-weight: 500; }
	.status-ok { color: var(--success-color); font-weight: 600; }
	.status-muted { color: var(--text-muted); }

	@media (max-width: 992px) {
		.feature-block {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
			gap: 2.5rem;
			margin-bottom: 4rem;
		}
		.feature-block.row-reverse { direction: ltr; }
	}
</style>
